  "text": "Hepatitis B virus (HBV) infection is a major global health problem frequently resulting in progressive, degenerative liver disease, including cirrhosis and hepatocellular carcinoma. Despite the availability of a safe and effective vaccine, and a range of nucleoside analogue antivirals, ,240 million people are chronically infected with HBV [CITATION_1] . The high rate of viral turnover has resulted in vaccinerelated escape mutants and drug resistance [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Therefore, development of safe, efficient antiviral strategies remains a key challenge for the treatment of HBV.",
